      "assignees": [],
      "body": "## Critical Issues\n\n- Issue #49: Context auto-compact functionality is stuck at 0% completion, preventing normal memory/context recovery.\n- Issue #46: JavaScript heap out-of-memory crashes occur during large MCP operations and extended sessions.\n\n## Impact Assessment\n\nThese critical defects create immediate user-facing reliability problems: memory exhaustion can make Claude Code unusable during active sessions, context auto-compact failures can block recovery on macOS platforms, and JavaScript heap crashes can force full restarts with lost workflow continuity. Issue #47 is also referenced because cross-project hook execution problems may affect the broader hotfix validation and release process.\n\n## Resolution Strategy\n\nImplement a hotfix priority workflow for v1.0.72 that documents memory optimization guidance, establishes context buffer management thresholds, introduces streaming-oriented mitigation for large operations, and tracks follow-up validation through the hotfix pull request. The planned approach references #49, #46, and #47 so issue resolution remains linked across the critical bug workflow.\n\n## Tracking Keywords\n\nmemory exhaustion, context auto-compact, JavaScript heap, hotfix priority",
